2. When would you prefer Excel over Power BI?

Excel wins for individual, ad-hoc analysis:

✅ Quick calculations (VLOOKUP, SUMIFs)
✅ Financial modeling (NPV, IRR)
✅ <100K rows (pivots still responsive)
✅ No IT support needed
✅ Offline work
✅ VBA automation

Power BI overkill: Personal budgeting, classroom grades, small team reports.



3. What is DAX and how is it different from Excel formulas?

DAX = Columnar calculation language optimized for analytics:

| Feature       | Excel Formula           | DAX                                                   |
| ------------- | ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| Con       | Cell-based =SUM(A1:A10) | Row/filter con [Total Sales] = SUM(Sales[Amount]) |
| Reusability   | Copy-paste per cell     | Single measure → All visuals                          |
| Performance   | Row-by-row              | Vectorized (millions of rows)                         |
| Relationships | Manual VLOOKUP          | Automatic via model                                   |

Same calculation:


=SUMIFS(Sales!B:B, Sales!C:C, ">2025-01-01")


YTD Sales = TOTALYTD(SUM(Sales[Amount]), Date[Date])



4. How does Power BI handle large datasets better than Excel?

Power BI's columnar storage + VertiPaq engine crushes Excel:


1M row sales data:
Excel → 15min pivot refresh → Crashes
Power BI → 3sec slicer response → Smooth

Technical advantages:

    Compression: 10x smaller file sizes

    In-memory: SSD-speed queries

    Aggregations: Pre-calculated summaries

    Query folding: Database pushes work

Excel limitation: Row-oriented storage → Sequential scans → Memory thrashing.



5. Explain one real-life use case where Power BI is better than Excel.

Scenario: 50 stores × 1M transactions/year = 50M rows

Excel approach (fails):


✅ Import 1st quarter (250K rows)
✅ Pivot crashes at 6 slicers
❌ Can't handle full year
❌ Manual monthly updates
❌ Email spreadsheets to execs

Power BI solution (production-ready):

✅ Connect live to SQL + POS systems
✅ Star schema: Sales → Store → Product → Date
✅ Executive dashboard: 12 slicers (Store/Region/Product/Category)
✅ Mobile layout for regional managers
✅ Daily auto-refresh 2AM
✅ Row-level security (Store123 sees own data only)
✅ Teams app distribution

Business impact:

Before Power BI: Monthly Excel → 2 days work
After Power BI: Real-time dashboard → 2min insights
ROI: ₹5Cr inventory optimization (3 months)

Decision Framework

<100K rows + Personal use → Excel
>1M rows + Teams → Power BI
Both skills → Hybrid (Excel → Power BI pipeline)

